title: Remembering Billie Holiday
description:
We remember the life of legendary jazz singer Billie Holiday, who died on July 17, 1959. We remember her rise to fame from the nightclubs of Harlem, as well as classic recordings of “Strange Fruit” and “God Bless the Child.” Despite a life that was filled with struggles, we are grateful Lady Day shared with us her unique voice.

Discover more about Billie Holiday's life: http://ow.ly/iRLD308zRGt

Music: "Even When We Fall" by Philipp Wiegl
http://freemusicarchive.org/music/Philipp_Weigl/Sound-trax/Philipp_Weigl_-_02_-_Even_when_we_fall
